      "writtenOn": "2019-07-17T02:06:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Should this enum include all possible results for all test types? \n\nFor example, more test result types are mentioned at: https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/master/docs/testing/json_test_results_format.md#Test-result-types",
      "revId": "ca40bde861bffb798145dbc679af1ba8dc87ae15",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4ba9455d_88f12469",
        "filename": "results/proto/v1/common.proto",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 54,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-17T06:53:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "it should cover all possible results, but not directly represent each result type of each test types. This wouldn\u0027t scale: it would mean each time we add a new test type, we might need to extend the enum. This would mean this enum is poorly designed.\n\nInstead, one enum member here may represent multiple result types of a particular test type. This way, a consuming layer does not have to distinguish between different test types. It still can, if it wants to, using tags, but does not have to.",
      "parentUuid": "b15775ee_8e0a6fb0",
      "revId": "ca40bde861bffb798145dbc679af1ba8dc87ae15",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
